Deep learning for the radiative transfer simulations
Meng Gao Updated March 8, 2020
* 1. Goal
** Train deep network for radiative transfer simulation
** Build the tool from simplest regression model
** Develop an easy follow workflow to tune hyperparamters
* 2. Radiative transfer model
** Use 5 submode to represent aerosol micro-physical properties
** Use wind speed(scalar), Chlorophyll a concentration to model ocean and surface scatterings
** Use principal componnet analysis to represent aerosol refractive index spectrum
** Random values of parameters are used to generate training dataset
* 3. Tools
** Pytorch
* 4. Reference
** Radiative transfer and aerosol retrieval algorithm
Meng Gao, Peng-Wang Zhai, Bryan Franz, Yongxiang Hu, Kirk
Knobelspiesse, P. Jeremy Werdell, Amir Ibrahim, Feng Xu, and Brian
Cairns, "Retrieval of aerosol properties and water-leaving reflectance
from multi-angular polarimetric measurements over coastal waters",
Optics Express Vol. 26, Issue 7, pp. 8968-8989 (2018)
https://doi.org/10.1364/OE.26.008968

